'No. —, Original.

John Doe, Demise of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, v. City of Rochester; and Commonwealth of Massachusetts v. Eugene Van Voorhis et al., Commissioners of Appraisal.

No. —, Original.

Argued April 24, 1922. Decided April 24, 1922. Mr. E. H. Abbott, Jr., for plaintiffs. Mr. Eugene Van Voorhis for Van Voorhis et al.

Motions for leave to file declarations herein denied, without prejudice to filing of motions for leave to file bills in equity for the same purpose.
